1 The legislature further finds that these constraints
2 undermine the councils' capacity to fulfill their statutory
3 responsibilities, delay decision-making, and frustrate Native
4 Hawaiian families and communities who seek the respectful
5 treatment of iwi kupuna.
6 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to strengthen the
7 island burial councils by:
8 (1) Extending the time to fill vacancies that occur during
9 a council member's term;
10 (2) Providing per diem compensation in the form of a
11 stipend for council members representing geographic
12 regions to improve recruitment and retention; and
13 (3) Adjusting the councils' quorum for business to be a
14 majority of the appointed council members, but no
15 fewer than three members.
16 SECTION 2. Section 6E-43.5, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
17 amended as follows:
18 1. By amending subsection (b) to read:
19 "(b) Appointment of members to the councils shall be made
20 by the governor, in accordance with section 26-34 and subsection
21 (a), from lists for each council submitted by the department and
