2 councils shall be submitted as follows:
3 (1) For vacancies attributable to the expiration of terms,
4 the list shall be submitted on the first business day
5 of December before the expiration of the terms, except
6 as provided in subsection (c); and
7 (2) For a vacancy that occurs during a council
8 [rcprcoGntativG’□] member's term, the list shall be
9 submitted within [thirty-buoincoo] seventy-five
10 calendar days after the vacancy occurs, except as
11 provided in subsection (c)."
12 2. By amending subsections (e) and (f) to read:
13 "(e) The department, in consultation with the councils,
14 office of Hawaiian affairs, representatives of development and
15 large landowner interests, and appropriate Hawaiian
16 organizations, such as Hui Malama I Na Kupuna 0 Hawai‘i Nei,
17 shall adopt rules pursuant to chapter 91 necessary to carry out
18 the purposes of this section. The council members shall serve
19 without [componoation,] salary, but shall be reimbursed for
20 necessary expenses incurred during the performance of their
21 duties. Council members appointed to represent geographic
