1 regions may receive a stipend for each day of attendance at a
2 duly noticed meeting, paid by the office of Hawaiian affairs.
3 The stipend amount, process, and eligibility reguirements shall
4 be determined by the board of trustees of the office of Hawaiian
5 affairs. In addition, council members shall be reimbursed for
6 necessary expenses incurred during the performance of their
7 duties. The councils shall be a part of the department for
8 administrative purposes.
9 (f) The councils shall hold meetings and acquire
10 information as they deem necessary and shall communicate their
11 findings and recommendations to the department. Notwithstanding
12 section 92-3, whenever the location and description of burial
13 sites are under consideration, the councils may hold closed
14 meetings. A majority of all members appointed to [whieh] each
15 council [-ie—shall constitute a quorum to do
16 businessf—]; provided that no fewer than three members shall
17 constitute a quorum to do business. Concurrence of a majority
18 of the members present at a meeting shall be necessary to make
19 any action of a council valid."
